author: blake-sc
message:
Suce 385 refactor for clarity around divisions (#261)

* Removed "unique counter" and uid adjustment. Uids should be pre-adjusted
in data.

* Renamed "root_file(s)" to "division_file(s)" as they do in fact point to
division files in the division subfolder. "root" is properly a reference
to the collection not the files.

* Set the first entry in a division file to type="division", the structure
of the files is such that the first entry is the division entry.

* Update menu query to use division type filter

* Add "type" index to "root" collection

* Added in logic to detect duplicate uids and spit out error messages
duplicate uids can cause failures later down the line so error seems
to be the appropriate logging level

* Fixes extremely frustrating bug, the query was running before the data
was actually inserted into the database, causing it to do nothing
or worse raise obscure exceptions.

* Remove hack to set division type: it should be set correctly in the data files
remove debugging message.

* Simplify submenu query

author: chansikpark
message:
Remove dependency on pali_concord.json

Instead, use `all_pali_concordance.json`.

Before, the PaliPageNumbinator loaded the contents of `pali_concord.json` into a dictionary that maps a tripleconsisting of the Mahasangiti volume code, paragraph number, and the manuscript edition codeto a couple consisting of the book and page number in the PTS manuscripts for the corresponding volume.

After this change, PaliPageNumbinator loads the contents of `all_pali_concordance.json` into a dictionary as before, but the key is a couple, omitting the manuscript edition code which the new loading algorithm will ensure is always a PTS edition. The loading algorithm also handles which PTS edition to use, always preferring the latest one.

(cherry picked from commit 7941b0b8c0f30719cbb43cbde4588532b4973f9d)
